Package: circlss
Type: Package
Title: Circular-Response Location-Scale Families for 'mgcv'
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: person("Ziwei", "Huang", email = "huang-ziwei@outlook.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Circular-response distributional families for the 'mgcv'
    general family interface, so that gam() can fit penalized-spline
    regression models (GAM/GAMLSS) with an angular response. Provides the
    von Mises family vmlss(), with a Fisher-Lee tan-half link for the mean
    direction and a log link for the concentration, each modelled by its
    own linear predictor. Log-likelihood derivatives to fourth order
    support full Newton REML smoothing-parameter selection. Numerical
    results are differentially tested against the 'pycircstat2' Python
    package, whose derivative implementations this package transcribes.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    mgcv (>= 1.9.4),
    stats
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    jsonlite,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
Config/testthat/edition: 3
URL: https://circstat.github.io/circlss/, https://github.com/circstat/circlss
BugReports: https://github.com/circstat/circlss/issues
